				posted 2004-08-19 08:54&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=bug&id=1080"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=bug&id=1074"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	http://www.java.com/<br />
click -- 'get it now'<br />
<br />
this is the ONLY Java VM one should use, and i'm 99%  sure the only LEGAL Java VM allowed in use today.<br />
<br />
Microsoft JVM used to be IE's default and come packaged with Windows, until courts proved it did some illegal things to try to take over Java from sun so Microsoft no longer supports MSJVM and people  must migrate/use the Sun Java VM from http://www.java.com/ <br />
<br />
the applet works fine here and for many people AFAIK<br />
<br />
pretty much any JRE (www.java.com again should auto-give you a good one) version 1.4.x or later should be good.<br />
<br />
Now there are some settings you may have incorrect for your plugin/shiz -- When you are at a page that uses java the 'java cup' icon should load in your system tray (typically bottom right hand corner of screen) -- Right click on that go to 'Control Panel'<br />
<br />
My Settings --<br />
BASIC<br />
Java Console [Hide Console]<br />
[X] Show Java in System Tray<br />
[ ] Show exception Dialog Box<br />
ADVANCED<br />
[Use Java Plug-in Default]<br />
BROWSER (check all that apply for you)<br />
[X] Microsoft Internet Explorer<br />
[ ] Netscape 6 or later <br />
[X} Mozilla 1.1 or later<br />
PROXIES<br />
[X] Use Browser Settings<br />
<br />
the rest shouldn't matter at all really but feel free to tweak them...the proxies one is sometimes very important, as well as the browser one and the advanced one. i would also always have 'Show Java in System Tray' selected ;)<br />
<br />
<br />
some excerpts from sites:<br />
# If you do not see the icon, go to Internet Explorer / Tools / Internet Options / Advanced and scroll down until you see the SJVM option. It will be immediately above Microsoft VM.<br />
# Make sure the box in front of the SJVM option is checked.<br />
# If there is no SJVM option, the program has not been installed<br />
<br />
# If SJVM is installed, but you cannot access [Applets], go to Start / Settings / Control Panel / Java Plug-In 1.4.x and make sure the following items have all been checked:  <br />
<br />
   1. Basic Tab: Enable Java Plug-In<br />
   2. Advanced Tab: Use Java Plug-In Default<br />
   3. Browser Tab: Microsoft Internet Explorer<br />
   4. Proxies: Use Browser Settings<br />
   5. Cache: Enable Caching <br />
<br />
Also, always make sure to click &quot;Apply&quot; =)<br />
You may also need to restart after installation (depending on OS)<br />
<br />
if you need, feel free to contact me by email and i'll probably help: lilmage55@cox.net			   <P align=right></P>
